data.name: radioButtonDCMotorOrBuzzer.ToolTip
data.value: Buzzer is a device that can produce sound by vibrating a diaphragm or a piezoelectric element. It is often used in alarms, timers, and other devices that require sound output. DC motors can also be used to produce sound by varying the speed of the motor, which changes the frequency of the sound produced. This is often used in applications such as electric toothbrushes, fans, and other devices that require variable speed control. It uses pin 8 in Arduino, GPIO 18 in Raspberry Pi, and pin 25 in ESP32.

data.name: radioButtonStepperMotor.ToolTip
data.value: Stepper motor is a motor that moves in discrete steps, allowing for precise control of position and speed. It is commonly used in applications such as 3D printers, CNC machines, and robotics where accurate movement is essential. Also, it can be used to generate sound by adjusting the speed of rotation to create different frequencies. It uses pin 9 for direction and pin 10 for step in Arduino, GPIO 21 for direction and GPIO 20 for step in Raspberry Pi, and pin 27 for direction and pin 26 for step in ESP32.
